<methods>
<methodStep>
<description>
<section>
<title>Experimental Design</title>
<para>Within a single, 75-yr old fire scar near Cherskii, Siberia, four stands varying in density/biomass were selected to determine carbon pools within above and belowground components. Within each stand, three 20 m x 2 (or 4 m) belt transects (i.e., plots) were established at least 20 m apart. We used narrower transects (2-m wide) for higher density stands, and wider transects (4-m wide) for lower density stands.</para>
</section>
<section>
<title>Methods</title>
<para>Soil horizon and thaw depths were measured along center of each belt transect (i.e., plot). Horizons were measured by gently exacavating a soil 'brownie' down to the mineral layer and then measuring the depth of green moss, soil organic layer, and leaf litter in the hole where the 'brownie' was removed. Thaw depth was measured by inserting a metal probe into soil until resistance (permafrost) was felt.</para>
</section>
</description>
